oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Hymnal, American Army of Occupation
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This hymnal, printed for the American Army of Occupation, Coblenz, Germany, and compiled by the Religious Work Department of the YMCA was provided to soldiers. The cover features a full color rendition of the 3rd Army insignia. On the inside front cover there is a laundry list handwritten in purple indelible pencil. The hymnal belonged to Cpl. Roy R. Stephens, Co. M, 117th Inf. Regt. and Co. H, 5th Inf. Regt. Stephens was from Crockett County, Tennessee.
